status_message:
Malaysian flight MH17 went down earlier today in Ukraine near the Russian border. The story's developing, but here's what we know so far:

-All 295 people aboard the flight were killed (280 passengers and 15 crew members).
-Reuters reported that 23 people on the plane were U.S. citizens.
-The plane departed from Amsterdam and was en route to Kuala Lumpur.
-An adviser to Ukraine's interior minister wrote on Facebook that a Buk antiaircraft missile used by pro-Russian rebels shot down the plane. 
-Rebels said the Malaysian plane was brought down by a Ukrainian SU-25 aircraft and have reportedly seized the plane's black box. 

Follow along for live updates: http://nyp.st/1rkAoNN

(AP Photo/Dmitry Lovetsky)
